+
+## Stable tmux backend
+
+`server.tmux.ts` keeps the terminal state inside a named tmux session instead of a one-off PTY process per browser connection.
+
+Why this matters:
+
+- the backend session survives browser disconnects
+- multiple viewers can attach to the same terminal state
+- you can drive the session directly with `tmux send-keys` even if browser automation/focus is flaky
+- Carbonyl can become a terminal viewer over a stable tmux-controlled Pi session
+
+### Run Pi behind the tmux backend
+
+From the monorepo root:
+
+```bash
+pnpm install
+pnpm build
+cd examples/local
+HOST=127.0.0.1 PORT=3001 TMUX_SESSION=cursed-pi TMUX_INIT_COMMAND=pi pnpm run tmux:dev
+```
+
+Useful environment variables:
+
+- `TMUX_SOCKET` — custom tmux socket path
+- `TMUX_SESSION` — tmux session name to reuse/create
+- `TMUX_SESSION_CWD` — working directory for the created session
+- `TMUX_INIT_COMMAND` — command started inside the tmux session, e.g. `pi`, `/bin/zsh`, `python3 -q`
+
+Status endpoint:
+
+- `http://127.0.0.1:3001/api/tmux/status`
+
+### Open it in Carbonyl
+
+```bash
+npx -y carbonyl http://127.0.0.1:3001
+```
+
+### Drive the backend directly through tmux
+
+```bash
+tmux -S "${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/claude-tmux-sockets/cursed-stack.sock" capture-pane -p -J -t cursed-pi:0.0 -S -200
+
+tmux -S "${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/claude-tmux-sockets/cursed-stack.sock" send-keys -t cursed-pi:0.0 -- 'say exactly OTTER_TMUX_OK' Enter
+```
+
+That lets the nested stack stay visible in Carbonyl while the authoritative control path is the tmux backend.
